# Architecture

## Monorepo layout

- app/ — Main Nuxt 4 application (UI + API + services + Prisma + tests)
- microservice/ — Companion service (Nitro/H3 server, Prisma, Redis, BullMQ helpers)
- scripts/ — Local automation and maintenance scripts
- .deploy/ — Kubernetes templates (envsubst-rendered), staging key rotation jobs/RBAC
- .github/ — Actions workflows and composite actions
- docs/ — Project documentation
- .cursor/ — AI agent rules and skills

pnpm-workspace.yaml defines two workspaces: app and microservice.

## Main application (app/)

- app.vue, layouts/, pages/ — Vue pages and layout
- components/ — Vue components (auth, headers, modals, admin, reports, profile, etc.)
- composables/ — Client composables (useAPI, useAppFetch, filters, snapshot mode, etc.)
- plugins/ — Nuxt plugins (api.ts, store init, snapshot menu, disable-lastpass)
- middleware/ — Client middleware (auth, admin)
- lib/ — Frontend utilities and shared logic (formatting, rounding, category filters, utils)
- schema/ — Zod schemas (schema/zod.ts, plaid.ts) + tests
- stores/ — Pinia stores (authStore, listStore) + tests
- server/
  - api/ — Nitro routes (REST-like). Example areas (not exhaustive):
    - Account invites, registers, entries, categories, budgets, savings goals
    - Auth and MFA flows, user profile
    - Reconciliation periods, reports, snapshots
    - Admin: users, accounts, audit logs, system status, job logs, Plaid data, openai logs, plaid sync logs
    - Tasks: backup, recalculate, sync-plaid, sync-google-sheets, bill reminders, etc.
    - Webhooks: Plaid
  - clients/ — prismaClient, redisClient, queuesClient, natsClient, postmarkClient, openaiClient
  - cron/ — Scheduled jobs (e.g., plaid daily/hourly, bill reminders hourly, recalculate hourly, backup daily, crypto-balance hourly)
  - lib/ — Server utilities (account membership/access, appUrl, handleApiError, mfa, pagination helpers, plaid helpers, queueManager, audit/integration logs, rateLimitRedis, JWT rotation, etc.)
  - middleware/ — Server middleware (auth, sitemap redirect)
  - plugins/ — Server plugins (graceful shutdown, initTestDate, queueManagerPlugin, security-headers)
  - queues/ — BullMQ queues (backupQueue, plaid sync queues, recalculateQueue)
  - routes/ — Extra routes like health and _nuxt asset serving
  - services/ — Core business logic
    - forecast/ — Forecasting domain: AccountRegisterService, ReoccurrenceService, RegisterEntryService, DateTime/Service, LoanCalculator, Transfers, Persist/Load, ModernCache, logger, rateLimiter, types
    - integrations — PlaidSyncService, PlaidTransactionEnrichmentService, PlaidReauthService, PlaidSyncNotificationService
    - notifications — notificationCenterService
    - reoccurrence health, reconciliation, reports, budget/category clone services, account/member/invite services, hashing/JWT/RSA services, asset valuation (Vehicle/AssetValueEstimate), AlchemyService (crypto)
  - env.ts, envSchema.ts — Environment configuration via Zod parsing
  - logger.ts — Server logging
- prisma/
  - schema.prisma — MySQL schema with enums, relations, and /// @encrypted annotations
  - migrations/ — SQL migrations (chronological)
  - reencrypt/ — Generated by prisma-field-encryption for field re-encryption
  - seed.ts — Seed data
- tests/
  - server/api/__tests__ — Rich API test suites (account, auth, budget, registers, reoccurrence, reports, tasks, health, etc.)
  - server/services/__tests__ — Unit/integration for services including forecast and integrations
  - e2e/ — Playwright tests/specs, snapshots, setup/teardown
  - lib/__tests__, schema/__tests__, stores/__tests__, pages/__tests__ — Unit tests
  - vitest.* configs, playwright.config.ts

## Microservice (microservice/)

- server.ts — Nitro/H3 server bootstrap
- routes/ — migrate.get.ts, migrate.post.ts, test.get.ts
- clients/ — prismaClient.ts, redisClient.ts
- lib/ — bull.ts (BullMQ helpers), normalizePrismaDmmf.ts
- prisma/ — Own schema.prisma (subset aligned with app), migrations, reencrypt/ (generated)
- scripts/ — k8s-rotate-db-key.sh for in-cluster key rotation (runner-keyrotate Docker target)
- logger.ts, server/logger.ts — Logging

Purpose:
- Support specialized operations such as DB key rotation and re-encryption flows
- Expose migrate endpoints used by the CronJob (staging) to rotate keys and trigger migrations

## Data flow highlights

- Frontend uses composables/useAPI.ts or useAppFetch.ts to call Nitro API routes under /api/*
- Server/api handlers use server/clients/prismaClient.ts and server/lib/* helpers to access DB, enforce access, and respond
- Background work via BullMQ queues (server/queues) and cron jobs (nuxt-cron) in server/cron
- Forecast engine orchestrates domain services with in-memory caching and persistence helpers
- Plaid integration via PlaidSyncService, webhook handlers, and enrichment service

## Encryption and keys

- prisma-field-encryption annotates encrypted fields (e.g., User.email, AccountRegister.name, RegisterEntry.description)
- prisma/reencrypt/ is generated to assist in migrating/re-encrypting fields
- Scripts and microservice CronJob (staging) rotate and re-encrypt keys safely

## Deployment pipeline (high level)

- Dockerfiles at app/Dockerfile and microservice/Dockerfile
- GitHub Actions build and push images to gcr.io (Build1/Build2);
- Main deploy job applies K8s manifests via .github/actions/deploy-dineros-gke using .deploy templates and envsubst
- Staging also builds a runner-keyrotate image and applies key-rotation CronJob/RBAC when configured

